svg.text: Three companies dominate the Chinese Internet:
Baidu is China’s largest search engine, Alibaba is
an e-commerce platform, and Tencent operates
the messaging services QQ and WeChat. However,
all three companies have developed assets
beyond their core businesses: Baidu, for example,
operates an online editable encyclopedia similar
to Wikipedia; Alibaba has expanded into mobile
payments and cloud computing; and Tencent
has through its investments become the world’s
The name Alibaba comes from “Ali Baba and the
Forty Thieves,” while Tencent’s Chinese name,
a nod to the company’s roots in messaging.
